            <thetext>Consider following situation:
An user downloads the skeleton and starts right away by executing

	make source
	
Instead of reporting the missing QOOXDOO_PATH ( &quot;Please configure QOOXDOO_PATH&quot; ) it does report

	&quot;make: Nothing to be done for `source&#39;.&quot;
	
The problem is that you only get the right error message when you execute &quot;make&quot; *without* any target.
The error message should be shown always (as long as the QOOXDOO_PATH is undefined) no matter what the user executes.</thetext>
